<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Susan Lynch</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">AFS0005</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Susan Lynch</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Written submission for the Commons Select Committee concerning Free School set up against the will of people of Stoke Poges.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Concerning: The process for approving, compelling and establishing academies and free schools, including working with sponsors;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I should like to tell you about this process in the case of the Khalsa Secondary School that has been opened in the village of Stoke Poges , Bucks despite strong objections from our population of about 5000 people.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">South Bucks has an excellent education system with a choice of good schools and enough places for all children</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The DfE web site states the following:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">“Free Schools are all-ability state-funded schools set up in response to what local people say they want and need in order to improve education for children in their community.”</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The DfE purchased an office block for use as a free school. It is situated on green belt land on a quiet road which has no footpath to the east side. We have poor public transport links. The school is needed for the children of Slough and it was stated in the application that it would be in the Slough Local Authority. We are in Buckinghamshire and as it is a Sikh faith school, very few local children will attend</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. The school will be for 850</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> pupils when it is fully operational</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Slough will not release land for more schools- I understand they need five new secondary schools. The plan</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is to transport 850</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> children from west London and Slough on roads that are rural, narrow and already very congested –especially near Wexham Park Hospital which would be on the route.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">An application was made to South Bucks District Council planning department for a large extension to the building and for change of use.  The planning officers and highways department recommended rejection as the site was on green belt, the highways unsuitable and transport plan unsustainable. At the last moment </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(just as the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> temporary permitted development act came in to operation) the DfE withdrew the planning application (with waste of public money) and have proceeded to purchase the building which is in an area of high property prices.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The school has </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">move</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> in on a “temporary” basis under the temporary permitted development right.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> It has children in year 7 and 8 only at present- less than 100 pupils. This must be a waste of public money.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As a result of this school opening in the village, all secondary school children living here will lose their right to free school transport.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The school itself may be very good but it is in the wrong place for this community, the pupils and for sustainability.</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>